# Grafana Dashboard Guidelines

## Dashboard Configuration
- **UID**: `microservices-monitoring-001`
- **Title**: "Microservices Monitoring & Performance Applications"
- **Tags**: prometheus, monitoring, kubernetes

## Template Variables
- `$app`: Application filter (auth, user, product, cart, order, review, notification, shipping, shipping-v2)
- `$namespace`: Namespace filter (service namespaces: auth, user, product, cart, order, review, notification, shipping, or monitoring for monitoring components)
- `$rate`: Rate interval (5m, 15m, 1h, 6h, 12h, 1d)

## Panel Layout
- **Width**: 12 (half) or 24 (full)
- **Height**: 8 (standard)
- **Row Groups**: Overview, Traffic, Errors, Runtime, Resources

## Legend Configuration
- **Display Mode**: Table
- **Placement**: Right
- **Calculations**: Mean, Max
- **Sort By**: Max (descending)

## Panel Descriptions
- **Required**: All panels must have descriptions
- **Format**: Concise and actionable
- **Content**: What it shows, why it matters, what to look for

## Color Thresholds
- **Green**: Good performance (0-1% error rate, < 300ms latency)
- **Yellow**: Warning (1-5% error rate, 300-1000ms latency)
- **Red**: Critical (> 5% error rate, > 1000ms latency)

## Units
- **Bytes**: Memory usage, network traffic
- **Short**: Counters, totals
- **reqps**: Requests per second
- **percent**: Success/error rates
- **ms**: Response times

## Query Patterns
- **Rate Queries**: Always use `$rate` variable
- **Aggregation**: `sum(...) by (app)` for overview
- **Filtering**: `{app=~"$app", namespace=~"$namespace"}`
- **Histogram Quantiles**: `histogram_quantile(0.95, sum(rate(...)) by (le))`

## Row Groups
1. **Overview & Key Metrics** (12 panels)
2. **Traffic & Requests** (4 panels)
3. **Errors & Performance** (5 panels)
4. **Go Runtime & Memory** (6 panels)
5. **Resources & Infrastructure** (5 panels)